Background:¶

The Movie Database (TMDB) is a community built movie and TV database. Every piece of data has been added by our amazing community dating back to 2008. TMDb's strong international focus and breadth of data is largely unmatched and something we're incredibly proud of. Put simply, we live and breathe community and that's precisely what makes us different.

Every year since 2008, the number of contributions to our database has increased. With over 400,000 developers and companies using our platform, TMDB has become a premiere source for metadata.

Along with extensive metadata for movies, TV shows and people, we also offer one of the best selections of high resolution posters and fanart. On average, over 1,000 images are added every single day.

We're international. While we officially support 39 languages we also have extensive regional data. Every single day TMDB is used in over 180 countries

INTRODUCTION¶

This project explains and analyzes the TMDB Dataset having more than 10,000 rows and their different attributes or features. The project is focusing more on the Genres, and questions raised tells the story of the genres of movies and the relationship between the sales,budget allocated and the poularity of the movies. It also take cognisance of the raings and how well the vieweres vote to the the correlation between the revenue, budget,the poularity of the movies. This project made use of pandas library Package to evaluate and clean the data and the in-built function of pandas are used for expolatory analysis and visualization. The Exploratory analysis ,the revenue trend from year to year and the questions are answered.

RESEARCH QUESTIONS¶

1.The Genres by the Total Revenue and Total Budget.

2.The Number Genres released.

3.The Genres of movies and the Runtime Duration.

4.Showing the Descriptive features of highly rated movies.

5.The Correlation Analysis of some of the different features.

6.The Top 10 Movies and their Ratings.

7.The Change of Revenues And Budget over Years.

8.The Most popular Genres over the Years.

9.Which Genres are most popular from year to year.

10.What Genres are more popular and their Ratings.

DATA CLEANING¶

A Lot of cleaning was done to prepare it for the expolatory process.

The dataset was checked for duplicates and only one duplicate was found.

The duplicate rows was dropped and also missing values was also discovered.

The data set had a total of 13,433 missing rows.

There were some columns that were needed for the analysis and a whole lot was dropped so we could foocus on the relevant data.

The columns budget and revenue was dropped and the other budget_adj and revenue_adj was chosen becaues in the dataset description it informs and shows the revenue and budget in terms of 2010 dollars accounting for inflation over time.

Two columns were renamed the budget_adj and the revenue_adj to budget and revenue.

The datatypes of the columns were changed from float64 to int64.

The overall descriptive analysis was extracted.

It was discovered thst some of the rows of the columns Runtime,Budget and Revenue had zeros values in them which did not reflect real time scenarios.

Those columns were replaced with np.nan and filled with the mean of the columns.

The genres column had its genres in a long string seperated by a character.

A copyof the DataFrame created so as to split and extract the individual genres seperating using the splits string and explode function

EXPLORATORY DATA ANALYSIS¶

QUESTION ONE:

What are the Genres that has Total Budget Allocation and Total Revenue Sales

OBSERVATIONS

This shows that Action,Dram and Adventure were allocated more budget in the movie production . While the Western and Tv Movie Genre had the lowest Budget Allocation. This shows the Genres and the Total Revenue made from box office sales. It shows that the Action movies clearly bring more Revenue,followed by the Adventure. While the Western and Tv Movie made the lowest revenue

#creating a barplot to display the total revenue and total budget of the gentes over the years
#using lambda to to get the two variables and the total sum  and grouping by the genres and sorting in descending 
plt.figure(figsize=(10,10))
genresBY_Values =df_tmdb.groupby('genres').apply(lambda x:x[['budget','revenue']].sum()).sort_values(['revenue','budget'],ascending = [False,False])
genresBY_Values.plot.bar(title = 'Genres By Total Budget and  Total Revenue',xlabel='Genres',ylabel =' Value')

QUESTION THREE:

Which Genres have a higher Runtime For Movies

OBSERVATIONS

The mean runtime was derived using the groupby function to to get the mean runtime of each of the genres.

This shows that War Genre have the highest runtime duration over two hours for all the Movie Genres

Wilst the western came second in runtime duration, Having a longer runtime duration doesnt mean the genres are more popular.

In [33]:

CONCLUSIONS¶

The revenue changed drastically over the year but showed an overall increase.

The 1960s accounts for the least budget allocated and revenue, while the 2010s accounts for the most.

The revenue of high revenue movie shows a strong positive correlation with budget and popularity, and a weak correlation with average voting and runtime.

More rutime duration doesnt conclude the movies are more popular to the viewers.

The most popular genre of the movie changed over the year and we can see that most movies gaines popularity after the year 2000.

The genres that have more longer runtime duration tend to be the least in revenue and also have low budget allocation.

The analysis does not state or imply that one change causes another based solely on a correlation.

That would require deeper statistical analysis that was not performed in this project.

LIMITATIONS

The Popularity and the runtime columns clearly have a large presence of outliers. As a result of the presence of outliers in the Popularity Column gettimg the mean popularity wouldnt give me a good statisticsal analysis.

The presence of zeros in the budget revenue ,budget_adj,revenue_adj and also in the runtime columns.

The Datasst contains so many missing values and in the cleaning process a lot of rows were dropped thus changing the shape of the Dataset.
